info.name: TotalDiscovery API
info.description:
TotalDiscovery use a classic REST/JSON model for our API. It uses easily understood resource-based routes that allow the URL to be a natural part of the user experience. It also uses a straightforward API token authentication model to make it easy and safe to get started right away. All request will return to you in JSON format including errors.

Using these API's, one can operate on important resources like Matters, Collections, Custodians, LegalHolds

**We are working hard create a better API experience across our entire app, but right now this version is a bit in flux.**

Let us know if you have issues or questions by contacting support.

Contact Support:
 Name: support
 Email: support@totaldiscovery.com

request.description:
Lists collections.

You can scope down this function further by either matter_id or custodian_id by passing in the relevant query parameter.

Sorting follows JSON API standard; reverse sorts are done by prefixing the sort parameter with "-". (TODO: Pull this out to a higher-level heading.)

Include parameters support custodian and collection_telemetry. (TODO: Pull out to a higher-level heading.)

Term filtering is available, and filters on collection and custodian name.

request.description:
Creates collections.

The supplied custodian and matter need to be in the same tenant.

Specification allows for the following options for each type:
- file: 'common', 'custodian-identified', 'network-collect', 'pictures', 'music', 'videos'
- email: 'exchange'

query.description:
Following the pattern in JSON API for the [Inclusion of Related Resouces](http://jsonapi.org/format/#fetching-includes), this allows you to ask for related objects to be filled in. 

For `/matters` this only works for `matters-contact`

Note: as the [JSON spec](http://jsonapi.org/format/#document-compound-documents) points out, the related objects will be placed in the `"included"` section of the return and not in line with the main object
A limit on the number of elements returned. It can be between 1 and 100, with the default typically being 10 items.
When using pagination, you should pass the number of items you would like to skip (ie, the number of items already received from a previous call).
